overview: Anthony is Director of Accounting Services at TempCFO Solutions successfully developing and navigating accounting infrastructures for a wide variety of clients. He has over 15 years of experience in interim accounting, assurance, tax, mergers and acquisitions for private and public companies and venture capital firms. With previous experience from KPMG and Ruzzo Scholl & Murphy, Anthony earned valuable and constructive public accounting experience, focusing on high-tech and manufacturing institutions. Subsequently, he managed his own practice for four years in which he worked extensively with some of the valley’s most successful startups such as Ironport Systems, Inc., which was part of an $835M merger with Cisco Systems in 2007. Anthony is a Certified Public Accountant and earned his Bachelors of Science degree in Accounting from California Polytechnic State University, San Luis Obispo.
